**Segments**

- **Deployment Type**: The hosted PBX market can be segmented based on deployment type into On-Premises and Cloud-Based. On-Premises solutions involve physical hardware installed onsite, providing complete control to the user. Cloud-based solutions, on the other hand, are hosted offsite, offering scalability, flexibility, and ease of management.

- **Organization Size**: This market segment categorizes users based on the size of the organization. It includes Small and Medium-sized Enterprises (SMEs) as well as Large Enterprises. SMEs typically opt for hosted PBX solutions due to cost-effectiveness and ease of setup, while large enterprises require scalable and feature-rich systems to meet their complex needs.

- **Industry Vertical**: The industry vertical segmentation of the hosted PBX market involves categorizing users based on the industry they belong to. This includes Healthcare, IT & Telecom, BFSI (Banking, Financial Services, and Insurance), Manufacturing, Retail, and others. Each industry has unique communication requirements, compliance regulations, and challenges that can influence the choice of a hosted PBX solution.

